    <p>In this tutorial, we'll learn how to style HTML tables using CSS. Each example includes code and the result displayed below it.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2>1. Basic Styled Table</h2>
    <p>We can style borders, padding, and text alignment using CSS.</p>

    <h3>Code Example:</h3>
    <pre><code>
table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 80%;
}

th, td {
    border: 1px solid #333;
    padding: 10px;
    text-align: left;
}

th {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: white;
}
    </code></pre>

    <h3>Result:</h3>
    <table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 80%;">
        <tr>
